Call Out					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																																												DESC:A well-crafted insult forces an opponent to duel you.																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.12	BENEFIT:As a standard action, you can make an Intimidate check against a hostile target within 30 feet that can clearly see and hear you. The DC of this check is equal to 10 + your opponent's Hit Dice + its Wisdom modifier. If the target is trained in Sense Motive, the DC is instead equal to 10 +your opponent's Sense Motive bonus, if higher. If you succeed at this check, the target enters a duel with you. The target cannot withdraw from the duel for 1 round + 1 round for every 5 by which the check beat the DC.
Leapfrog					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Performance																	PRESKILL:1,Acrobatics=3										PRETEXT:Acrobatics 3 ranks.								DESC:You can use an opponent as a springboard.																																				SOURCEPAGE:p.15	BENEFIT:When you spend a swift action to attempt a performance combat check after a successful charge attack or combat maneuver, you gain a +2 bonus on your performance combat check and gain a +4 bonus on your next Acrobatics, Climb, Fly, Ride, or Swim check attempted before the end of your next turn.
Improved Parry				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Combat Expertise																					PRETEXT:Int 13, Combat Expertise.	PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_INT,13	DESC:A flick of the wrist binds your opponent's weapon.																																		SOURCEPAGE:p.12	BENEFIT:When you successfully parry a foe's melee attack (with a dueling parry or the parry class feature), your next melee attack against the target does not allow the enemy to apply its Dexterity bonus to AC (if any). This attack must be made before the end of your next turn.
River Raider				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat																																												DESC:You are skilled at creeping up on watercraft without being noticed, then swiftly leaping over the side and into combat.	BONUS:SITUATION|Survival=Forage in or near rivers and streams,Swim=In calm or rough water|4							SOURCEPAGE:p.24	BENEFIT:You gain a +2 bonus on Swim and Stealth checks while swimming in calm or rough water. In addition, if you're able to act in a surprise round and start it in water, you can take both a move and a standard action. You still can't take a full-round action during the surprise round. [Normal] You can take only a move or a standard action during a surprise round in which you can act.
Second Wind					CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat.Performance		PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Endurance																						PRETEXT:Endurance.									DESC:The roar of the crowd strengthens your resolve.																																			SOURCEPAGE:p.15	BENEFIT:When you spend a swift action to attempt a performance combat check, you gain a +2 bonus on your performance combat check, and if you are shaken,sickened, or fatigued, these conditions are suppressed until the end of your next turn.
Sweeping Dodge				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:Combat				PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=FEAT,Dodge																							PRETEXT:Dex 13, Dodge.			PREVARGTEQ:PreStatScore_DEX,13	DESC:A quick sweep of your cloak deflects an incoming attack.																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.12	BENEFIT:When you make a dueling dodge while wearing a cloak, you gain evasion (as the rogue ability). If a critical hit or sneak attack is scored on you, there is a 25%% chance that the critical hit or sneak attack is negated and damage is instead rolled normally. This feat only applies until the attack that triggered the immediate action is resolved. This feat does not stack with the fortification armor special ability or similar effects.
Waterway Caster				CATEGORY:FEAT		TYPE:General																																											DESC:You have learned to cast spells while sailing on or swimming in even the most turbulent waters.																											SOURCEPAGE:p.25	BENEFIT:You automatically succeed at any concentration checks required to cast a spell while being subjected to vigorous or violent motion while either swimming or on a ship. You gain a +4 bonus on concentration checks to cast spells underwater.

